---
description: Flow — spec-driven workflow toolkit
alwaysApply: true
---

Flow is a spec-driven workflow for AI coding agents. It moves changes through
`drafting` → `building` → `closed`.

To invoke a Flow command, run the canonical Flow shape:

```
FLOW_HOST=cursor flow <command>
```

If `flow` is not on `PATH`, install the Flow CLI, then retry.

Render public Flow commands with slash-command `/flow-*` syntax when
recommending the user's next command.

Supported commands: `setup`, `doctor`, `roadmap`, `run`, `run all`, `start`,
`amend`, `plan`, `build`, `build-task`, `test`, `close`, `status`.

Treat the driver's stdout as the Flow envelope and follow it exactly. Flow
never runs `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, `gh`, or `glab`. Do not create
repository history directly; the only allowed commit paths are a printed
`flow run --checkpoint <run-dir> --milestone M-N` command during a
roadmap run and the run-closing commit `flow run --finalize` creates
itself, both with checkpoint commits enabled.
